# Create Analyze Rule

Use when analyzing code quality, fixing issues, or preparing Go code for commit.

## Commands

### Static Analysis

```bash
go vet ./...
```

Finds: suspicious constructs, unreachable code, incorrect printf calls.

### Format Code

```bash
gofmt -w .
# or
goimports -w .
```

Formats all Go files and organizes imports.

### Build

```bash
go build -o /tmp/masterfabric-server ./cmd/server
```

Compile and check for errors without running.

### Run Tests

```bash
go test ./...
go test -v ./internal/...
go test -race ./...          # Race condition detection
go test -cover ./...         # Coverage report
```

### Lint (if golangci-lint installed)

```bash
golangci-lint run ./...
```

### Database Migrations

```bash
# Apply migrations
goose -dir internal/infrastructure/postgres/migrations postgres "$DATABASE_URL" up

# Rollback last migration
goose -dir internal/infrastructure/postgres/migrations postgres "$DATABASE_URL" down

# Check status
goose -dir internal/infrastructure/postgres/migrations postgres "$DATABASE_URL" status
```

### Dependency Management

```bash
go mod tidy        # Remove unused, add missing
go mod download    # Download dependencies
go mod verify      # Verify dependencies
```

## Typical Workflow

1. Make code changes
2. `go vet ./...` - fix any issues
3. `gofmt -w .` - format code
4. `go build ./cmd/server` - verify compilation
5. `go test ./...` - run tests
6. `go mod tidy` - clean dependencies

## Common Fixes

- Add missing error checks
- Remove unused variables/imports
- Fix incorrect struct tags
- Add missing `context.Context` parameter
- Fix nil pointer dereferences

## Checklist

- [ ] `go vet ./...` passes with no errors
- [ ] `go build` compiles successfully
- [ ] `go test ./...` all tests pass
- [ ] `go mod tidy` applied
- [ ] No unused imports or variables
